cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.RO 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with dense pixel matching, which is an important task in computer vision. The use of neural networks and convolutional layers also suggests that it could belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The development of a novel neural network layer also suggests that it could belong to the neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the application of the SDC descriptor network to stereo matching and optical flow algorithms suggests that it could belong to the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category.
